{"id":236486,"date":"2024-02-02T13:10:37","date_gmt":"2024-02-02T07:40:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=236486"},"modified":"2024-02-02T17:54:07","modified_gmt":"2024-02-02T12:24:07","slug":"aditya-srivastava","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/","title":{"rendered":"Aditya Srivastava Wiki, Height, Age, Wife, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-236652\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava\" width=\"414\" height=\"464\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-268x300.jpg 268w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 414px) 100vw, 414px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Aditya Srivastava is an Indian actor, who predominantly works in Hindi television series and films. He is well known for playing the role of Senior Inspector Abhijeet in the popular police procedural TV show &#8216;C.I.D&#8217; (1998-2018), which aired on Sony Entertainment Television.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce01a2b1aa\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce01a2b1aa\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Wife_Children\" title=\"Wife &amp; Children\">Wife &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Theatre\" title=\"Theatre\">Theatre<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Film\" title=\"Film\">Film<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Television\" title=\"Television\">Television<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Awards\" title=\"Awards\">Awards<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#Nominated\" title=\"Nominated\">Nominated<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aditya-srivastava\/#FactsTrivia\" title=\"Facts\/Trivia\">Facts\/Trivia<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Aditya Srivastava was born on Sunday, 21 July 1968 (<strong>age 55 years; as of 2023<\/strong>) in Allahabad (now Prayagraj), Uttar Pradesh. His zodiac sign is Cancer. He pursued his bachelor&#8217;s degree from Allahabad University, Prayagraj.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Height (approx.):<\/strong> 5&#8242; 10&#8243;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour: <\/strong>Black<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour:\u00a0<\/strong>Black<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/full-image-of-Aditya-Srivastava.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-236796\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/full-image-of-Aditya-Srivastava.jpg\" alt=\"full image of Aditya Srivastava\" width=\"352\" height=\"519\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/full-image-of-Aditya-Srivastava.jpg 542w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/full-image-of-Aditya-Srivastava-203x300.jpg 203w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 352px) 100vw, 352px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span>Family<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>His father&#8217;s name is D.N. Srivastava.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236654\" style=\"width: 434px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-father.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236654\" class=\" wp-image-236654\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-father.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava with his father\" width=\"424\" height=\"257\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-father.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-father-300x182.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-father-768x466.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 424px) 100vw, 424px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236654\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava with his father<\/p><\/div>\n<p>He has a brother named Ashutosh Srivastava, he is an assistant director.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236655\" style=\"width: 311px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-brother-Ashutosh-Srivastava.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236655\" class=\" wp-image-236655\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-brother-Ashutosh-Srivastava.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava brother Ashutosh Srivastava\" width=\"301\" height=\"383\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-brother-Ashutosh-Srivastava.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-brother-Ashutosh-Srivastava-236x300.jpg 236w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 301px) 100vw, 301px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236655\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava brother Ashutosh Srivastava<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Wife_Children\"><\/span><strong>Wife &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Aditya Srivastava got married to a psychologist named Manasi Srivasatava in 2003. It was an arranged marriage. Together, they have two daughters named\u00a0<span class=\"LrzXr kno-fv wHYlTd z8gr9e\">Arushi Srivastava and Adwika Srivastava.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236656\" style=\"width: 249px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-wife.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236656\" class=\" wp-image-236656\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-wife.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava with his wife\" width=\"239\" height=\"455\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-wife.jpg 420w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-his-wife-158x300.jpg 158w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 239px) 100vw, 239px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236656\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava with his wife<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Theatre\"><\/span><strong>Theatre<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Aditya Srivastava started his career as a theatre artist at Sangeet Samiti,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><\/sup> Civil lines, Allahabad, while pursuing his bachelor&#8217;s degree. In 1989, he moved to Delhi, where he started performing with Shri Ram Centre for Performing Arts.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Film\"><\/span><strong>Film<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Aditya Srivastava made his Bollywood debut with the 1994 film &#8216;Bandit Queen&#8217; in which he played the role Puttilal. In 1996, he acted in the film &#8216;Sanshodhan,&#8217; starring <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/manoj-bajpayee\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manoj Bajpayee<\/a>. His performance as Inspector Khandilkar in the film &#8216;Satya&#8217; (1998) received immense appreciation from the audience.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236657\" style=\"width: 439px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Satya.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236657\" class=\" wp-image-236657\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Satya.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava in a still from the film 'Satya'\" width=\"429\" height=\"342\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Satya.jpg 753w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Satya-300x239.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 429px) 100vw, 429px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236657\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava in a still from the film &#8216;Satya&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 2000, he played the supporting role of Tito\u00a0in the film &#8216;Dil Pe Mat Le Yaar.&#8217; Earlier, he was offered to play the lead role in the film, however, it was later given to <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/manoj-bajpayee\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manoj Bajpayee<\/a>. Srivastava appeared as a guitarist named Murgi in Anurag Kashyap&#8217;s film &#8216;Paanch,&#8217; made in 2001. Though the film was never released in theatres, it was shown as the closing film in Osian&#8217;s Cinefan Festival of Asian and Arab Cinema in 2005.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236658\" style=\"width: 279px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Paanch.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236658\" class=\" wp-image-236658\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Paanch.jpg\" alt=\"Poster of the film 'Paanch'\" width=\"269\" height=\"382\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Paanch.jpg 563w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Paanch-211x300.jpg 211w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 269px) 100vw, 269px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236658\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Poster of the film &#8216;Paanch&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>He appeared as Lt. Col. Pradeep in the <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/hrithik-roshan\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hrithik Roshan<\/a> starrer film &#8216;Lakshya&#8217; (2004).\u00a0He appeared as a lead actor for the first time in the film &#8216;Dil Se Pooch&#8230; Kidhar Jaana Hai&#8217; in 2006. He essayed the role of a police officer named Avinash in the film.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236660\" style=\"width: 594px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-film-Dil-Se-Pooch.-Kidhar-Jaana-Hai.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236660\" class=\" wp-image-236660\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-film-Dil-Se-Pooch.-Kidhar-Jaana-Hai.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava (left) in a still from the film 'Dil Se Pooch... Kidhar Jaana Hai'\" width=\"584\" height=\"279\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-film-Dil-Se-Pooch.-Kidhar-Jaana-Hai.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-film-Dil-Se-Pooch.-Kidhar-Jaana-Hai-300x143.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-film-Dil-Se-Pooch.-Kidhar-Jaana-Hai-768x367.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 584px) 100vw, 584px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236660\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava (left) in a still from the film &#8216;Dil Se Pooch&#8230; Kidhar Jaana Hai&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>He essayed the role of Karan Singh in the film &#8216;Gulaal&#8217; in 2009. He played the lead role of Sameer in the 2010 film &#8216;Kaalo.&#8217; In 2019, he appeared as Lallan Singh in the film &#8216;Super 30.&#8217; In 2024, he appeared as Bansi Sahu in the Netflix film &#8216;Bhakshak.&#8217;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236663\" style=\"width: 557px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Bhakshak.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236663\" class=\" wp-image-236663\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Bhakshak.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava in a still from the film 'Bhakshak'\" width=\"547\" height=\"338\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Bhakshak.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Bhakshak-300x185.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Bhakshak-768x474.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 547px) 100vw, 547px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236663\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava in a still from the film &#8216;Bhakshak&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Some of his other Hindi films include &#8216;Dil Se..&#8217; (1998), &#8216;Saathiya&#8217; (2002), &#8216;Black Friday&#8217; (2004), &#8216;Raat Akeli Hai&#8217; (2020), and &#8216;Bheed&#8217; (2020).<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236670\" style=\"width: 510px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Black-Friday.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236670\" class=\" wp-image-236670\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Black-Friday.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava in a still from the film 'Black Friday'\" width=\"500\" height=\"295\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Black-Friday.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Black-Friday-300x177.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-film-Black-Friday-768x453.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236670\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava in a still from the film &#8216;Black Friday&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Apart from Hindi films, he has also appeared in a few Tamil films such as &#8216;Naalai&#8217; (2006) and &#8216;Aalwar&#8217; (2007).<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236671\" style=\"width: 348px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Aalwar.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236671\" class=\" wp-image-236671\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Aalwar.jpg\" alt=\"Poster of the film 'Aalwar'\" width=\"338\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Aalwar.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Poster-of-the-film-Aalwar-255x300.jpg 255w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 338px) 100vw, 338px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236671\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Poster of the film &#8216;Aalwar&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Television\"><\/span><strong>Television<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>He made his television debut with the television series &#8216;Dera&#8217; in 1992. He played the role of Madhumoy Sur in the episode &#8216;Kahen Kavi Kalidas&#8217; of the TV show &#8216;Byomkesh Bakshi&#8217; (1994), which was broadcast on the channel DD National.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236675\" style=\"width: 522px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Byomkesh-Bakshi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236675\" class=\" wp-image-236675\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Byomkesh-Bakshi.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava (left) in a still from the TV series 'Byomkesh Bakshi'\" width=\"512\" height=\"342\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Byomkesh-Bakshi.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Byomkesh-Bakshi-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Byomkesh-Bakshi-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236675\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava (left) in a still from the TV series &#8216;Byomkesh Bakshi&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 1997, he acted in the television drama series &#8216;9 Malabar Hill&#8217; in which he essayed the role of Majid. The television series was aired on the channel Zee TV. Srivastava acted in a few episodes of the thriller horror television\u00a0anthology series &#8216;Aahat&#8217; (1998), which aired on Sony Entertainment Television.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236752\" style=\"width: 481px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Aahat.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236752\" class=\" wp-image-236752\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Aahat.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava in a still from the TV series 'Aahat'\" width=\"471\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Aahat.jpg 725w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-Aahat-300x248.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 471px) 100vw, 471px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236752\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava in a still from the TV series &#8216;Aahat&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>He gained immense popularity after he played the role of Senior Inspector Abhijeet in the popular police procedural TV series &#8216;C.I.D&#8217; (1998-2018), which aired on Sony Entertainment Television. He was selected by B. P. Singh to play the role of Abhijeet after Singh noticed him in the film &#8216;Satya&#8217; (1998). Before playing Abhijeet, he played as a criminal named Paresh in the episode &#8220;The Case of the Stolen Gun&#8221; of the series.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236777\" style=\"width: 564px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-as-Abhijeet-in-a-still-from-the-TV-show-C.I.D.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236777\" class=\" wp-image-236777\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-as-Abhijeet-in-a-still-from-the-TV-show-C.I.D.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava (left) as Abhijeet in a still from the Tv show 'C.I.D'\" width=\"554\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-as-Abhijeet-in-a-still-from-the-TV-show-C.I.D.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-as-Abhijeet-in-a-still-from-the-TV-show-C.I.D-300x171.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-as-Abhijeet-in-a-still-from-the-TV-show-C.I.D-768x437.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 554px) 100vw, 554px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236777\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava (left) as Abhijeet in a still from the Tv show &#8216;C.I.D&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 2004, he played the role of Pramod in the horror television series &#8216;Raat Hone Ko Hai,&#8217; which aired on the channel Sahara Manoranjan. He worked as a narrator for the historical TV drama series &#8216;Peshwa Bajirao&#8217; (2017), which was broadcast on Sony Entertainment Television.\u00a0In 2019, he essayed the role of Inspector Ashfaq Ali Khan in the television series &#8216;CIF,&#8217; which aired on Dangal TV.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_236785\" style=\"width: 497px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-CIF.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236785\" class=\" wp-image-236785\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-CIF.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava (left) in a still from the TV series 'CIF'\" width=\"487\" height=\"316\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-CIF.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-CIF-300x195.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-left-in-a-still-from-the-TV-series-CIF-768x498.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 487px) 100vw, 487px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236785\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava (left) in a still from the TV series &#8216;CIF&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>He has also made guest appearances in several shows such as &#8216;Jeena Isi Ka Naam Hai&#8217; (2007) on Zee TV, &#8216;Comedy Circus Ka Naya Daur&#8217; (2011) on Sony Entertainment Television, &#8216;Adaalat&#8217; (2012) on Sony Entertainment Television, and &#8216;Kaun Banega Crorepati (Season 8)&#8217; (2014) on Sony Entertainment Television.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Awards\"><\/span>Awards<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Nominated\"><\/span><strong>Nominated<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ipc-inline-list__item\" role=\"presentation\"><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">Best Actor in a Supporting Role at Indian Telly Awards 2005 for his performance as Abhijeet in the TV series &#8216;C.I.D&#8217;\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">Best Actor in a Supporting Role at Indian Telly Awards 2006 for his performance as Abhijeet in the TV series &#8216;C.I.D&#8217;\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ipc-inline-list__item\" role=\"presentation\"><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\"><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">Favourite Actor &#8211; TV at <\/span><\/span>Nickelodeon Kids&#8217; Choice Awards 2013 for his performance as Abhijeet in the TV series &#8216;C.I.D&#8217;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ipc-inline-list__item\" role=\"presentation\"><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">Best Supporting Actor: Web Original Film at Filmfare OTT Awards 2020 for the film &#8216;<\/span>Raat Akeli Hai&#8217;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ipc-inline-list__item\" role=\"presentation\"><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">Most Popular Supporting Actor in a Digital Film at IWM Digital Awards 2020 <\/span>for the film &#8216;Raat Akeli Hai&#8217;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ipc-inline-list__item\" role=\"presentation\"><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">Best Performance by an Ensemble Cast at FOI Online Awards 2020 <\/span>for the film &#8216;Raat Akeli Hai&#8217;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ipc-inline-list__item\" role=\"presentation\"><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">Best Performance by an Ensemble Cast\u00a0<\/span><span class=\"ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__li awardCategoryName\">at FOI Online Awards 2023 <\/span>for the film &#8216;Bheed&#8217;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FactsTrivia\"><\/span>Facts\/Trivia<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>In 1995, he moved to Mumbai, where he worked as a voice over artist for several advertisements and promos.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Initially, Aditya Srivastava was signed to act in 26 episodes in the TV series &#8216;C.I.D.&#8217; However, he later it was extended and he became an integral part of the television series.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>His name was entered into the Guinness Book of World Records for filming the lengthiest continuous shot in the &#8220;The Inheritance&#8221; episode of C.I.D.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In an interview, he revealed that many times people mistook him as a real police officer. He recalled an incident happened with him at the Delhi airport and said that a lady mistaken him as a cop and asked him to found her missing purse.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He is good friends with Dayanand Shetty for more than 20 years.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_236799\" style=\"width: 309px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-Dayanand-Shetty.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-236799\" class=\" wp-image-236799\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-Dayanand-Shetty.jpg\" alt=\"Aditya Srivastava with Dayanand Shetty\" width=\"299\" height=\"460\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-Dayanand-Shetty.jpg 520w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Aditya-Srivastava-with-Dayanand-Shetty-195x300.jpg 195w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 299px) 100vw, 299px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-236799\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aditya Srivastava with Dayanand Shetty<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Aditya Srivastava is an Indian actor, who predominantly works in Hindi television series and films. He is well known for playing the role of Senior Inspector Abhijeet in the popular police procedural TV show &#8216;C.I.D&#8217; (1998-2018), which aired on Sony Entertainment Television. Wiki\/Biography Aditya Srivastava was born on Sunday, 21 July 1968 (age 55 years; as of 2023) in Allahabad (now Prayagraj), Uttar Pradesh. His zodiac sign is Cancer. He pursued his bachelor&#8217;s degree from Allahabad University, Prayagraj. Physical Appearance Height (approx.): 5&#8242; 10&#8243; Hair Colour: Black Eye Colour:\u00a0Black Family Parents &amp; Siblings His father&#8217;s name is D.N. Srivastava. He <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":61,"featured_media":236652,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/236486"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/61"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=236486"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/236486\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":236970,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/236486\/revisions\/236970"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/236652"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=236486"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=236486"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=236486"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}